headline.main: Debutantes to Assist War Relief Party Of English-Speaking Union at 'The Wookey'

lead_paragraph: Of the many benefit theatre parties of late Autumn contributing to Anglo-American interests and war-relief activities, one of the most largely subscribed is that of the English-Speaking Union for Thursday night's performance of "The Wookey," at the Plymouth Theatre, which deals with England in wartime.
